[[File:Soukass.JPG|thumb|A view of souk Al Asr]]
'''Souk Al Asr''' ({{lang-ar|سوق العصر}}; English: Era market) is one of the [[Souks of Tunis|souks]] of [[Tunis]], specialized in selling antique products. The souk is mainly intended for the middle class and poor.
== Location == It is located behind [[Bab Al Gorjani]], one of the [[Medina of Tunis|medina]]'s doors and near three neighbourhoods inhabited by poor people of Tunis, i.e. Mellassine, Saida Manoubia and Helal City.<ref name="aa">{{cite web|language=fr|author=Yousra Ouannes|title=Tunisie : " Souk al-Asr ", la brocante des pauvres|url=http://aa.com.tr/fr/mode-de-vie/tunisie-souk-al-asr-la-brocante-des-pauvres/72945|website=aa.com.tr|date=21 February 2015|access-date=23 January 2016}}</ref>
== History == The souk didn't exist before the [[Husainid Dynasty|Husainid era]] (1705-1957), while other souks emerged under the [[Hafsid dynasty]] (1228-1537).<ref name="aa"/> It was a tiny souk that stood between prayers of the afternoon and the sunset (third and fourth prayers of the day).<ref name="aa"/>
== Products == Souk Al Asr is totally the opposite of its own name as it solds only old products like household utensils, antique furniture and other rare items. This market is full of items that can be particularly useful and rare, that are not likely to be found elsewhere.<ref name="aa"/>
